ains."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Pattaya Night Bazaar", "description": "Tidy, central and open nightly on Second Road near Central Festival. Souvenirs, leather and a food court. The convenient tourist-friendly choice."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Made in Thailand Market (M.I.T.)", "description": "Nightly clothing and gadget market on Second Road behind Big C Extra, with a covered food zone. Best for shopping; bargain hard."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "The Sky Gallery / Lan Po Naklua stalls", "description": "Evening seafood and street stalls in Naklua with Gulf-of-Thailand sunset views. Quieter and more romantic than the city markets."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "Soi Buakhao street-food strip", "description": "A dense nightly run of stalls and small markets — the real locals' canteen. ฿50 plates, no shopping, central. Best for pure street food."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "Jomtien Beach Road stalls", "description": "Casual evening grills and dessert carts along the beachfront, busiest at weekends. Sea-view snacking with a ฿60 plate of grilled seafood."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 7, "name": "Theprasit souvenir lane", "description": "A touristy offshoot of the weekend Thepprasit crowd, leaning into elephant trousers, snacks and gifts. Good for last-day souvenir shopping."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 8, "name": "Pattaya Floating Market", "description": "A built attraction on Sukhumvit (~฿200 entry) with boats, walkways and stalls. Photogenic and family-friendly rather than a true bargain market."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 9, "name": "Naklua Market (evening)", "description": "A fresh market whose cooked-food and seafood stalls come alive in the early evening. Almost no tourists and local prices — the most authentic option."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 10, "name": "Walking Street & Beach Road vendors", "description": "Late-night carts an