 "Answer", "text": "Made in Thailand Market (M.I.T.) and the Pattaya Night Bazaar, both on Second Road, are best for shopping — clothes, gadgets, leather goods and souvenirs, open nightly. Thepprasit is cheapest for clothing in bulk but weekend-only. Bargain hard at all three; M.I.T. has the most inflated opening prices."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Are Pattaya night markets safe and hygienic?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "They're generally safe and busy. For food hygiene, stick to stalls with a queue and high turnover, make sure grilled items are cooked through, and avoid pre-cut fruit sitting in the sun. Keep an eye on your bag in crowds, test any electronics before paying, and use shared ฿10–30 songthaews rather than overpriced private quotes."}}]}]$b$);
