<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p><b>Yes — 7 days in Pattaya under ฿15,000 (~$420) is realistic</b>, excluding international flights. A daily budget of ~฿2,100 covers a hostel or cheap hotel (<b>฿350–650</b>), street food (<b>฿250</b>), local transport (<b>฿80</b>), one paid activity (<b>฿400–600</b>), drinks and a buffer. Stay in <b>Soi Buakhao</b> or a Jomtien hostel, eat at <b>night markets</b>, ride <b>baht buses</b> (฿20), skip Walking Street drinks, and <b>splurge once</b> on day 4 (paramotor or a seafood feast). You'll still finish the week with money to spare.</p>
</div>
</div>
