<div class="compare-foot">7-day total: ฿13,140 spent · ฿1,860 buffer remaining inside the ฿15,000 budget.</div>
</div>
<p>Result: <strong>฿13,140 spent, ฿1,860 buffer.</strong> Most travellers absorb ฿800–1,200 in unexpected items — a second massage, that overpriced cocktail you talked yourself into on day 4, an extra bottle of sunscreen. Even with all of those, you land under ฿15,000.</p>
<div class="callout warn">
<div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-scam-alert"></use></svg></div>
<div><h4>The budget killers to skip</h4><p>Five things quietly double a week if you don't see them coming: <strong>Walking Street cocktails</strong> (฿250+ vs ฿80 at a Soi Buakhao open-air bar), <strong>Beach Road seafront restaurants</strong> (2× markup — the view is free from the public sand), the <strong>tourist-menu trick</strong> (ask "Mee menu Thai mai?" for the ฿50 menu), <strong>paid airport transfers</strong> (the Bell 389 bus from Suvarnabhumi is ฿130, not ฿1,200), and <strong>jet-ski rentals on Pattaya Beach</strong> — the damage-deposit scam is still alive; book a paramotor instead.</p></div>
</div>
<!-- SAVE MORE -->
<h2 id="save-more">Save even more — long-stay + low-season</h2>
<p>If your dates are flexible, three tricks push the same week comfortably under <strong>฿11,000</strong>. None of them change your quality of life — they just reward planning ahead.</p>
<div class="money-grid">
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Long-stay discount</div><div class="val">−฿100/night</div><p>Hostels and condos drop sharply at 14 nights. MD Hostel falls from ฿350 to ฿250; a View Talay monthly hits ฿8,000 (฿267/night) with pool and kitchen.</p></div>
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Low season + weekdays</div><div class="val">−30–45%</div><p>Aim for May, June, September or October. Off-season hotel doubles drop from ฿1,400 to ฿650 — ฿325 a head with a partner.</p></div>
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Cook one meal a day</div><div class="val">−฿100/day</div><p>With an Airbnb kitchen, rice + eggs + greens + chilli paste is ฿20 a meal vs ฿120 at a stall. Over two weeks that's ฿1,400 saved.</p></div>
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Free walking tours</div><div class="val">฿0–200</div><p>Tip-based Pattaya Free Walking Tours run 2.5 hours through Old Pattaya and Naklua. Every Buddhist temple is free to enter.</p></div>
</div>
<p>If you'd rather splurge differently, three swaps we'd actually book: the <strong>paramotor flight</strong> (฿2,500, the one we keep coming back to), a <strong>dinner cruise past Koh Larn at sunset</strong> (฿1,800, buffet plus a drink), or a <strong>seafood feast at Lalin Seafood in Naklua</strong> (฿1,400 for two — whole grilled sea bass, tom yum goong, crab and beers). Pick one, place it on day 4 or 5, and you've still earned it. For more on planning the rest of your week, start at the <a class="inline" href="01-homepage-v5.html">Go To Pattaya homepage</a>.</p>
<div class="callout tip">
<div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-coins"></use></svg></div>
<div><h4>The genuine low-budget week</h4><p>Low season + a 14-night condo + cooking one meal a day + tip-based tours = <strong>฿9,800 for seven days</strong>. We've hit this twice. The quality of life is identical to the ฿15,000 week — you just plan ahead and ride the low season.</p></div>
</div>
<!-- FAQ -->
<h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq">
<div class="faq-item open">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">Is a ฿15,000 Pattaya week realistic? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Yes — for one person across seven nights, excluding international flights. The sweet spot is around ฿2,000–2,100 per day all-in: a hostel or shared hotel bed, three meals (one of them Western), local baht buses, one paid activity, drinks and a buffer. We have re-run this budget on nine trips since 2022 and come in between ฿11,950 and ฿14,810 every time. ฿15,000 is the ceiling, not the target.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">Is a ฿15,000 Pattaya week possible with kids? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Yes, but it tightens fast. A family of three can do it if you book a family room at MD Hostel (about ฿700 a double) and eat all meals at street markets. Add ฿2,000 to your buffer for kid-friendly activities and you are still inside ฿20,000 for the week. Skip Cartoon Network Amazone at full price (฿1,400 per kid) — go on a discount day instead.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">Can I eat Western food on this budget? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Occasionally. A pasta plate at a normal Thai-run Italian runs ฿180–250, a sandwich at 7-Eleven about ฿55. Skip Beach Road and Walking Street Western restaurants — the same plate is double. One Western meal a day is doable; three a day breaks the budget.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">Can I drink alcohol on a ฿15,000 budget? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Yes, but stay out of Walking Street. A Chang at 7-Eleven is ฿55. A bottle of Sangsom rum from Big C is ฿285 and lasts three nights. Soi Buakhao open-air bars charge ฿80 for a Leo, not ฿250. Budget about ฿200 a night for drinks and you will be fine.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">What's the best month for budget travel in Pattaya? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">May, June and September. Low-season hotel rates drop 30–45 percent, tours run at half-empty discounts, and weekday rooms are cheapest. Avoid December 20 to January 5 and Chinese New Year week, when rates double. October is rainy but the cheapest month overall.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">Hostel or cheap hotel — which is better value? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Hostel if you are solo (฿350–500 a night for a dorm, A/C, breakfast often included). A cheap hotel if you are two people sharing a ฿600–800 double — split two ways you land at ฿300–400 per person with a private bathroom and pool. We default to MD Hostel solo and an off-season hotel double for couples.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">What about ATM fees in Pattaya? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Every Thai ATM charges ฿220 per foreign-card withdrawal — non-negotiable, set by the bank. Withdraw the maximum (usually ฿20,000–30,000 depending on the bank) once, not ฿2,000 seven times. AEON ATMs at Big C and Tesco Lotus charge the same ฿220 but give a slightly better rate. A Wise or Revolut card saves you the conversion margin.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">Should I go cashless or carry cash in Pattaya? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Carry cash. Street food, baht buses, night markets, most cheap hostels, scooter rentals and massage shops are cash only. Cards work at malls (Central Festival, Terminal 21), 7-Eleven and big chains. Plan on cash for about 70 percent of your daily spend — keep ฿2,000 on you and the rest in the hostel safe.</div></div>
</div>
</div>
<!-- AUTHOR BIO -->
<div class="bio author">
<div class="ava">DR</div>
<div class="who">
<b>Daniel Reyes</b>
<span class="role">Travel editor · Go To Pattaya</span>
<p>Daniel plans budgets, transport and itineraries across Chonburi and has done nine separate budget trips to Pattaya, six of them under ฿2,200 a day. He pays for every hostel bed himself, books no comped activities, and double-checks every price by walking in and asking — the numbers here were verified between May 4 and May 28, 2026.</p>
</div>
</div>
