have re-run this budget on nine trips since 2022 and come in between ฿11,950 and ฿14,810 every time. ฿15,000 is the ceiling, not the target."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Is a ฿15,000 Pattaya week possible with kids?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, but it tightens fast. A family of three can do it if you book a family room at MD Hostel (about ฿700 a double) and eat all meals at street markets. Add ฿2,000 to your buffer for kid-friendly activities and you are still inside ฿20,000 for the week. Skip Cartoon Network Amazone at full price (฿1,400 per kid) — go on a discount day instead."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Can I eat Western food on this budget?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Occasionally. A pasta plate at a normal Thai-run Italian runs ฿180–250, a sandwich at 7-Eleven about ฿55. Skip Beach Road and Walking Street Western restaurants — the same plate is double. One Western meal a day is doable; three a day breaks the budget."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Can I drink alcohol on a ฿15,000 budget?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, but stay out of Walking Street. A Chang at 7-Eleven is ฿55. A bottle of Sangsom rum from Big C is ฿285 and lasts three nights. Soi Buakhao open-air bars charge ฿80 for a Leo, not ฿250. Budget about ฿200 a night for drinks and you will be fine."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What's the best month for budget travel in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "May, June and September. Low-season hotel rates drop 30–45 percent, tours run at half-empty discounts, and weekday rooms are cheapest. Avoid December 20 to January 5 and Chinese New Year week, when rates double. October is rainy but the cheapest month overall."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Hostel or cheap hotel — which is better value?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Hostel if you are solo (฿350–500 a night for a dorm, A/C, breakfast often included). A cheap hotel if you are two people sharing a ฿600–800 double — split two ways you land at ฿300–400 per person with a private bathroom and pool. We default to MD Hostel solo and an off-season hotel double for couples."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What about ATM fees in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Every Thai ATM charges ฿220 per foreign-card withdrawal — non-negotiable, set by the bank. Withdraw the maximum (usually ฿20,000–30,000 depending on the bank) once, not ฿2,000 seven times. AEON ATMs at Big C and Tesco Lotus charge the same ฿220 but give a slightly better rate. A Wise or Revolut card saves you the conversion margin."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Should I go cashless or carry cash in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Carry cash. Street food, baht buses, night markets, most cheap hostels, scooter rentals and massage shops are cash only. Cards work at malls (Central Festival, Terminal 21), 7-Eleven and big chains. Plan on cash for about 70 percent of your daily spend — keep ฿2,000 on you and the rest in the hostel safe."}}]}]$b$);
