<h3>Paramotor &amp; sky diving</h3>
<div class="rest-stat">
<span class="s"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16 is-muted"><use href="#pg-pin"></use></svg> Jomtien / Pattaya Sky Dive</span>
<span class="dot"></span><span>Cancelled 50%+ of wet days</span>
</div>
<p>Both have strict wind and visibility limits, and monsoon afternoons routinely exceed them. Paramotor flights are scrubbed more than half the time; sky diving is worse once you add cloud cover. You'll often pay, travel out, and be turned back at the gate. Genuinely one to save for a dry-season return.</p>
<div class="callout warn" style="margin:0">
<div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-shield-alert"></use></svg></div>
<div><h4>Don't push a borderline call</h4><p>If an operator is willing to fly you in marginal wind, that's a red flag, not a bonus. Reputable shops cancel and refund.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</article>
<!-- 2 -->
<article class="rest" id="skip2">
<div class="rest-grid">
