</div>
<p>There is no sunset to cruise into under monsoon cloud, and the water is often choppy — cruise companies will still run them because they want your money. Don't. For Koh Larn, cut a full day to a <strong>morning</strong>: most rainy afternoons there turn into a wet ferry ride home. Diving still works, though — wreck dives off Koh Sak are sheltered and run year-round.</p>
