<figure class="art-hero"><img alt="Is pattaya safe 2 – IsPattayaSafe? An Honest 2026 Safety Guide" fetchpriority="high" height="506" loading="eager" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/is-pattaya-safe-2.webp" width="1100"/>
      <figcaption class="cap"><span class="lead"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-pin"></use></svg> Pattaya Bay at dusk — safe to walk along Beach Road most evenings</span><span class="credit">Go To Pattaya</span></figcaption></figure>
<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p><b>Yes — Pattaya is generally safe for tourists.</b> The real risks are <b>property crime</b> (pickpocketing, scams) and, by a wide margin, <b>scooter accidents</b> — not violent crime, which is statistically rare at <b>0.38 incidents per 1,000 arrivals</b>. Use <b>Grab or Bolt</b> instead of unmetered tuk-tuks, don't rent a scooter without a licence, watch your drink on <b>Walking Street</b> late, and save <b>1155</b> (Tourist Police). Do that and almost every trip ends without incident.</p>
</div>
</div>
